w 10$^{-16}$ s$^{-1}$ for Hall effect to be efficient in disc\nformation. We conclude that Hall effect produces small $\\lesssim$10--20 AU\ndiscs regardless of the polarity of the magnetic field, and that radially\noutward diffusion of magnetic fields remains crucial for disc formation and\ngrowth.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Sep 2020 16:40:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-17"}
